definitions.definition: A political , cultural or social entity or part thereof that is completely surrounded by another.
examples: The republic of San Marino is an enclave of Italy.
The streets around Union Square form a Protestant enclave within an otherwise Catholic neighbourhood.

definitions.definition: A group that is set off from a larger population by its characteristic or behavior .
An isolated portion of an application 's address space , such that data in an enclave can only be accessed by code in the same enclave.
